          <div id="panel4" class="accordion-content" data-tab-content>
            HTML (HyperText Markup Language), CSS (Cascading Style Sheets), and JavaScript are cornerstone technologies used by websites. HTML determines the foundational structure and content of web pages. Web browsers then refer to CSS to define the look and layout of the text and other material. Finally, JavaScript enables a majority of the interaction between the user and the webpage. Without JavaScript, a majority of responsive effects would be unavailable. In terms of a human analogy, HTML is the skeleton, CSS is the skin, and JavaScript is the muscles of a web application.
