        <p>There were several key decisions made when considering the purpose and goals of this website.
        My goal was to have heavy emphasis on design, and a lighter touch on server-side logic. Sinatra was an obvious choice because of how lightweight it is compared to Rails. While Rails is powerful, it’s MVC architecture is unnecessarily complex for a site primarily focused on design. The decision to use Sinatra allowed for faster development.</p>
        <p>Foundation as a fronted framework was an important choice on the structure of the site. Because of Foundation, the site became defined by Foundation’s grid-system, and a majority of the CSS effects became possible of Foundation libraries. The main header, orbit box, and containers all heavily utilized Foundation libraries.</p>
        <p>JavaScript was used for features such as auto rotating through images and having a header that sticks to the top of the page.</p>
